---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Common Myths - Quiet the Mind">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <Hero
    title="Debunking Common Myths ✨"
    subtitle="Let's separate fact from fiction about intrusive thoughts and mental health."
  />

  <Section
    title="Myth vs. Reality"
    subtitle="Understanding the truth can reduce shame and self-blame:"
  >
    <div class="space-y-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="MYTH: 'I must be crazy'"
          icon="❌"
          class="border-red-200 dark:border-red-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Having intrusive thoughts means there's something seriously wrong with my mental health.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card
          title="REALITY: You're completely normal"
          icon="✅"
          class="border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Studies show that 94% of people experience intrusive thoughts. They're a normal part of human cognition.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="MYTH: 'Thoughts predict actions'"
          icon="❌"
          class="border-red-200 dark:border-red-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Having violent or disturbing thoughts means I'm likely to act on them.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card
          title="REALITY: Thoughts ≠ Actions"
          icon="✅"
          class="border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            People with intrusive thoughts are actually LESS likely to act on them because they find them so distressing.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="MYTH: 'I should control my thoughts'"
          icon="❌"
          class="border-red-200 dark:border-red-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            I should be able to stop these thoughts if I try hard enough.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card
          title="REALITY: Thoughts come and go naturally"
          icon="✅"
          class="border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Trying to control thoughts often makes them stronger. Acceptance and letting go is more effective.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="MYTH: 'These thoughts reveal my true self'"
          icon="❌"
          class="border-red-200 dark:border-red-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            My intrusive thoughts show what I really want deep down.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card
          title="REALITY: They're often the opposite"
          icon="✅"
          class="border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Intrusive thoughts typically go against your values, which is why they're so distressing.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    title="The Truth About Intrusive Thoughts"
    bgColor="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-gray-800"
    centerContent={true}
  >
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="They're Universal"
          icon="🌍"
          variant="highlighted"
          description="Research shows intrusive thoughts occur across all cultures, ages, and backgrounds."
        />
        <Card
          title="They're Temporary"
          icon="⏰"
          variant="highlighted"
          description="Like all thoughts, intrusive thoughts come and go. They don't last forever."
        />
        <Card
          title="They're Treatable"
          icon="🩺"
          variant="highlighted"
          description="Effective treatments exist, including therapy, mindfulness, and lifestyle changes."
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    title="Changing Your Perspective"
    centerContent={true}
  >
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <Card
        title="A New Way of Thinking"
        icon="🔄"
        variant="minimal"
        class="text-center"
      >
        <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
          <p>
            Instead of asking "Why am I having these thoughts?" try asking "How can I respond to these thoughts in a healthy way?"
          </p>
          <p>
            Remember: The goal isn't to never have intrusive thoughts - it's to have a healthier relationship with them.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
          <Button href="/strategies" variant="primary">
            Learn Healthy Responses
          </Button>
          <Button href="/resources" variant="secondary">
            Get Support
          </Button>
        </div>
      </Card>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</MainLayout>